    "summary": "Meteorologist and Physicist with a  analytic and problem solving mindset and an interest in educational development and communication.\nThe common theme in my career is investigating and communicating in (operational) meteorology and climate, setting up new training material/lessons/products and being an intermediar between KNMI and all kind of clients within and outside our institute.\n\nAs a meteorology student I became interested in practical research and all kinds of questions amongst meteorology: e.g: \" Can we understand and predict dynamical processes in the atmosphere especially related to convection\u201d.\n\nAs a Msc student I have searched for meteorological beauty at the IMAU in Utrecht. I looked e.g. into a data set of ECMWF and studied correlations between unbalanced regions in the upper troposphere in relation to formation of convergence and divergence zones in the lower parts due to gravity wave inition.   The first part of my working carrier I did a lot of operational work at the Dutch commercial weather service, Meteo Consult in Wageningen. Meanwhile I also really enjoyed to pick up educational tasks as well. I worked in small projects and finally I developed commercial meteorology courses for several groups and companies in the Netherlands. \nIn 2005 I had chosen to teach Physics at the Broklede High school in Breukelen for one year. At the same time  I worked at the University of Utrecht  to get my first degree teaching qualifications in Physics. \nIn 2006  I returned back in the field of meteorology within KNMI. I work part time as a trainer/developer and part time as an aviation meteorologist (till 2017) in the central forecast office in De Bilt.\nIn addition to these activities, I was a board member of the NVBM till 2016 and helped to  organize activities that call attention to diversity in the playfield of meteorology.  ",
